{"editorCode":";     Square and negative numbers\n\n;Lila created the procedure \"square_a\" and she wanted to run it with the value :a=100. By mistake, she wrote -100 instead of 100 and she run \"square_a -100\". The result was something unexpected. \n;Why did the bird designed the square like that?\n\n;Click the papyrus on the left to read the activity instructions.\n\n;---------PROCEDURES-------------\nTo square_a :a\nrepeat 4[fd :a rt 90]\nend\ncs\nsquare_a 100\nsquare_a  -100\n\nTo square_b :x\nrepeat ...\nend\ncs\nsquare_b ...\n\n;-----------------------------------\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.289101893839319e-14,"z":210.52631578947367},"character":"Bird","notes":" Instructions \n------------------------------------\na) Define the procedure squre_a and run it with parameter value 100 and -100. Can you explain the way the bird designed the second shape? \n\n To define the procedure, select the lines from the word \"TO\" to the word \"END\" and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nTo run the procedure, click on the line \"square_a 100\"and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \nDo the same for the line \"square_a -100\"\n\nb) Complete the procedure \"square_b \" using the command bk (back) instead of the command fd (forward) so that the bird designs the same shape with the procedure \"square_a\"\nRedefine the procedure square_b, run it, enable the sliders tools and change the limits of the slider :x to -200 and 200.\nDoes the bird design the same shape with the procedure \"square_a\" for all the different values of :x?  ?\n\nc) If the command  \"rt 90\" in procedure \"square_a\" changes to \"lt -90\", what shape will the bird design?  \nMake this change and check your ideas by redefining and running the procedure.","sliders":{},"objects":[]}